## Flux vs ArgoCD — Key Difference to Mention

```
ArgoCD                              FluxCD
──────────────────────────          ──────────────────────────
Compares Git vs cluster directly    Delegates to Helm upgrade
Self-heals any drift                Only syncs on chart version change
No version bump needed              Must bump Chart.yaml version
Single Application CR               GitRepository + HelmRelease (2 CRs)
```

> "Unlike ArgoCD which compares Git directly against the cluster and
> self-heals any drift, Flux delegates to Helm's upgrade mechanism.
> This means you must bump the chart version in Chart.yaml for Flux
> to trigger a Helm upgrade — just changing values.yaml is not enough."

